<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="External_links">External links</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Inform&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.firthworks.com/roger/cloak/inform/index.html">Cloak of Darkness: Inform</a> presents the same, short game implemented in both Inform 6 and Inform 7, as well as other languages for comparison.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.inform-fiction.org/inform6.html">Inform 6</a> - Official web site</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.firthworks.com/roger/informfaq/index.html">Inform 6 FAQ</a> at Roger Firth's IF Pages provides details on programming in Inform 6.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://inform7.com/">Inform 7</a> - Official web site.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.dmoz.org/Games/Video_Games/Adventure/Text_Adventures/Design_and_Development/Authoring_Systems/Inform">Inform</a> at <a href="/wiki/DMOZ" title="DMOZ">DMOZ</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://mirror.ifarchive.org/">The Interactive Fiction Archive</a> provides many Inform tools, examples, and library files.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://playfic.com/">Playfic</a> is a web-based interface for creating and sharing new games using Inform 7.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.guncho.com/">Guncho</a> is a multiplayer interactive fiction system based on Inform 7 with a combination of <a href="/wiki/MUD" title="MUD">MUD</a>-like and web-based interfaces.</li>
</ul>


